{"response":{"status":"ok","userTier":"deprecated","total":4698,"startIndex":21,"pageSize":20,"currentPage":2,"pages":235,"orderBy":"newest","tag":{"id":"sport/cycling","webTitle":"Cycling","type":"keyword","sectionId":"sport","sectionName":"Sport","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/cycling","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/sport/cycling","references":[]},"results":[{"webTitle":"Chris Froome withdraws from Tirreno-Adriatico with back injury","webPublicationDate":"2014-03-07T19:28:00Z","sectionName":"Sport","sectionId":"sport","id":"sport/2014/mar/07/chris-froome-withdraws-tirreno-adriatico-injury","fields":{"shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/3ncdv","standfirst":"• Team Sky confirms Australian Richie Porte will replace Briton<br />• Geraint Thomas to take over as team leader in France","hasStoryPackage":"false","body":"<p>Chris Froome, the Tour de France champion, has withdrawn from the Tirreno-Adriatico due to joint inflammation in the lower back, Team Sky have confirmed. The Australian Richie Porte has moved from their Paris-Nice squad to replace the Briton in Italy, with Geraint Thomas taking over as team leader in France.</p><p>Team Sky's Dr Alan Farrell said: \"Chris has suffered a slight inflammation to the sacroiliac joint in the lower back. As a precaution we have chosen to withdraw him from the Tirreno-Adriatico so he can focus on recovering for the Volta a Catalunya.\"</p><p>Froome took to Twitter to express his disappointment at missing out but accepted it was the right decision. He posted: \"Slight inflammation in my lower back, so I'll be putting my feet up for a few days on doctors' orders. No racing for me in Tirreno next week. It's disappointing to miss out on a week of solid racing, but&nbsp;rather safe than sorry at this point of the season.\"</p><p>Team Sky's performance manager,Rod Ellingworth, added: \"This is just a minor setback for Chris and we hope he will get back to full training within a week. He's obviously disappointed tomiss Tirreno-Adriatico but we shouldn't take any chances at this stage of the season.\"</p><p>The injury comes three weeks after Froome made an ideal start to his 2014 by retaining his Tour of Oman title with a 26-second lead over the American Tejay van Garderen. This year's Tour de France begins with a Grand Départ from Yorkshire on 5&nbsp;July.</p>","headline":"Chris Froome withdraws from Tirreno-Adriatico with back injury","trailText":"Team Sky has confirmed that Chris Froome has withdrawn from the Tirreno-Adriatico due to joint inflammation in the lower back","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/3/7/1394219743033/Tour-of-Oman---Day-Six-006.jpg","wordcount":"247","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-03-10T19:16:51Z"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2014/mar/07/chris-froome-withdraws-tirreno-adriatico-injury","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/sport/2014/mar/07/chris-froome-withdraws-tirreno-adriatico-injury","tags":[{"id":"sport/chris-froome","webTitle":"Chris Froome","type":"keyword","sectionId":"sport","sectionName":"Sport","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/chris-froome","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/sport/chris-froome","references":[]},{"id":"sport/team-sky","webTitle":"Team Sky","type":"keyword","sectionId":"sport","sectionName":"Sport","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/team-sky","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/sport/team-sky","references":[]},{"id":"sport/cycling","webTitle":"Cycling","type":"keyword","sectionId":"sport","sectionName":"Sport","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/cycling","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/sport/cycling","references":[]},{"id":"sport/sport","webTitle":"Sport","type":"keyword","sectionId":"sport","sectionName":"Sport","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/sport","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/sport/sport","references":[]},{"id":"tone/news","webTitle":"News","type":"