the same season.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2013/sep/24/bradley-wiggins-world-time-trial\" title=\"\">Wiggins wants to be remembered as one of the best time-trial riders cycling has produced</a>, and he hopes this will help him earn that status.</p><p>He has three Commonwealth silver medals. Two came at the 2002 Games in Manchester, when he lost out in the individual pursuit to Bradley McGee of Australia and where he was part of an England quartet who took silver behind Australia in the team pursuit. He made his Commonwealth debut in 1998 in Kuala Lumpur, at the age of 18, not long after winning gold at the world junior pursuit championships, taking silver in the team pursuit and fourth in the individual.</p><p>\"I haven't got a gold medal from the Commonwealths so it would be nice to add that on, and it's a couple of days after the Tour [de France] so for the sake of carrying on for a few more days and doing it,\" the 33-year-old Olympic champion told the <a href=\"http://www.cyclingnews.com/\" title=\"\">cyclingnews.com</a> website.</p><p>At four days, the gap between the end of the Tour on 27 July and the Games time trial this summer is shorter than the nine-day interval between <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2012/jul/22/bradley-wiggins-tour-de-france-cavendish\" title=\"\">the finish of the 2012 Tour de France</a> and the <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2012/aug/01/bradley-wiggins-gold-medal-olympian\" title=\"\">Olympic time trial</a> in London, both of which Wiggins won convincingly. The time trial in Glasgow will be 40km, starting and finishing at Glasgow Green and incorporating a single loop through East Dumbartonshire and North Lanarkshire as well as the city's East End. The British time trials are in Monmouthshire at the end of June.</p><p>Wiggins has already said that, in order to build as thoroughly as possible for the world time trials at the end of September in Spain, <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2014/feb/09/bradley-wiggins-vuelta-a-espana?INTCMP=ILCNETTXT3487\" title=\"\">he intends to ride the Tour of Spain in late August and September</a> although this would mean he would be unable to defend his title in the Tour of Britain.</p><p>Wiggins felt that he was short of racing when he took the silver medal in the world championships to the German Tony Martin. \"I'd love to go and do the Vuelta and use it as preparation for the world championships, and go down that route as Fabian [Cancellara] and Tony tend to do every year and really try to have a good crack.\"</p>","headline":"Bradley Wiggins confirms desire to ride at Commonwealth Games","trailText":"Bradley Wiggins confirmed that he intends to ride at the Commonwealth Games in Glasgow","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Sport/Pix/pictures/2012/7/27/1343412673789/Bradley-Wiggins-005.jpg","wordcount":"419","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-02-28T10:43:33Z"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2014/feb/25/bradley-wiggins-commonwealth-games-cycling","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/sport/2014/feb/25/bradley-wiggins-commonwealth-games-cycling","tags":[{"id":"sport/bradleywiggins","webTitle":"Sir Bradley Wiggins","type":"keyword","sectionId":"sport","sectionName":"Sport","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/bradleywiggins","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/sport/bradleywiggins","references":[]},{"id":"sport/commonwealthgames2014","webTitle":"Commonwealth Games 2014","type":"keyword","sectionId":"sport","sectionName":"Sport","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/commonwealthgames2014","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/sport/commonwealthgames2014","references":[]},{"id":"sport/commonwealth-games","webTitle":"Commonwealth Games","type":"keyword","sectionId":"sport","sectionName":"Sport","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/commonwealth-games","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/sport/commonwealth-games","refer